what are your favourite ways to give someone a non body based compliment?
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it's my favourite way to compliment my friends and family! people are so much more than their body! 
compliments are free, from the heart and have the #PowerToTransform someone’s mood! I’m excited to partner with @Pantene on this campaign because I truly believe compliments have the power to transform someone’s day.
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments actually go a long way in CONNECTING ourselves to others. A @pantene study found that 77% of canadians have felt disconnected from their friends and family during this time and yet 79% of canadians found a compliment can go a LONG way to making them feel better.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
compliments that are genuine are never superficial and never get old. on top of that, we should be giving them to ourselves too! 
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
make someone's day a bit brighter! #PowerToTransform #partner #ad

abuse girls face on social media. Every day girls are physically threatened, racially abused, sexually harassed and body shamed.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Girls from across the world have written an open letter to Instagram, Facebook, TikTok and Twitter, calling on them to create stronger and more effective ways to report abuse and harassment. Sign their open letter now – link in my story – and show that thousands of people stand with girls #FreeToBeOnline online, they’ll be taken seriously #StoptheSetback

node.text: my general take on what’s happening as of now. of course i didn’t get to say everything that i wanted to say and didn’t say everything right. it is a WILD time that we are living in. be prepared to be uncomfortable. be grateful we all still have internet, running water and food. (some of us actually still don’t have those things) and most of all, be grateful we have each other. it sounds corny as hell, but you don’t have your food or toilet paper or internet or water without the help of another human. don’t buy 250 rolls of toilet paper, it’s not the diarrhea boogeyman coming for you. also, what happens after this? do we go back to normal life? will there be a normal life? do you even WANT your normal life back? this is going to be a huge shift for many of us. your emotional shit is going to come up because we don’t have the same comforts as before. be kind and stay vigilant and stay aware! ✌️💕

when the break up starts feeling good.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was driving yesterday in vancouver and i started to cry a little bit. the sun was setting and the mountains were just over to my left. it wasn’t so long ago i was curled up in a ball on the floor of my apartment in toronto. feeling so much pain from my break up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i made myself a pact on day 2. i think it was because of how much pain i was in and how much it scared me. i told myself i have to become something from this, i have to become better. i couldn’t let this eat me up.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
so nightly i would close my door. light a candle. crawl to the floor and meet her. i’d ask questions that i knew had no answers. i’d try and rush it. i would try and journal her away, meditate her away, exercise her away. but eventually, you end up in this quiet place where you can only meet her. you deny nothing and accept pain as it is.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this last week i’ve been to secret caves. forests that have stories thousands of years old. allowed the ocean to hug me. and she isn’t around. i know pain always eventually comes back. but i’m grateful for the lightness.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you’re going through existential pain, keep going.
i know it’s hard, dark and endless.
i know that our brains trick us into thinking it will be forever.
i know that existential pain is exhausting and you’re so tired.
it’s okay to be tired.
just keep going.
be tired and continue to meet your existential pain. continue to know her. continue to see her.
this is what makes you brave.
and all of us brave broken hearted know one another in someway.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
keep going.
eventually you’ll cry from the lightness too ☀️
#breakups #selfgrowthjourney

node.text:
i regularly mute people when i come online.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s not a malicious act.
it’s not because i hate anyone.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it’s because i know when i start feeling bad about myself it’s time to turn *inward* instead of *outward.* constantly looking at everyone else’s stories and not my own can really mess with my head.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this hasn’t been confirmed but i’m 99% positive that our nervous systems are not meant to handle the thousands of stories we subject it to every single day.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
on top of that, social media is designed to be addictive as possible. it’s a hyper competitive space and extracts our attention. which is a finite resource. social media engineers are literally racing to the bottom of your brain stem. i recommend listening to tristan harris and daniel schmachtenberger talk at length on the neurohacker podcast.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
so i mute my friends.
i force quietness on an app that is designed for clamour and noise
i remind myself how lucky i am to be here.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i refuse social media’s lure to consume everything.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
muting people is okay if you need a break.
rest.
chill.
turn inward 🌱
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#selfgrowthjourney

node.text:
political perfectionism needs to honestly stop.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
perfectionism doesn’t help anyone, especially yourself if you’re recovering from something.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the perfectionism comes from the fact that we truly want to do so good. our hearts just want the best. we just want to *avoid* pain or discomfort by avoiding failure or error.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but the whole point of recovery is to fail. it’s to ask for help. it’s to own your shit.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and i cannot tell you how often i have had convos with people in recovery who feel like they cannot express their true thoughts because they are nervous they are going to be perceived as a bad person.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
the “bad” in us, whatever it is, NEEDS to be expressed in an environment that is designed to contain it. it needs to be messy, imperfect, crass, gross, shameful, ALL of it so we can get through it and out to another side.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“bad” stuff inside of us grows.
it speaks.
it growls.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you do not take it for a walk and allow it out to breathe, it will plant it’s roots.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
political perfectionism absolutely does not help mental health/illness spaces.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
find people who can hold you and contain you in your mess, getting through it so you can get to a different space ❤️
📸 - @aliciathurstonphotography

node.text:
sometimes i wonder where the fuck am i going with all this.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
where is my life headed?
what am i doing?
what people am i doing it with?
how is any of this real?
did the universe really wake up to itself in me?
why is my desire for certainty so painful?
where did the human condition start?
why am i so impatient with lines?
how come we never talk to each other?
how come i remember the smell of my 5th birthday but i can’t remember the stuff that broke me?
will i ever see japan?
will i throw my phone into the ocean and say goodbye to all of you?
why did i pick food instead of booze?
do i always have to be politically correct or is that another strive for perfectionism?
where am i going with all of this?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i think it’s normal to be confused, frustrated and lonely.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i know i’m confident. and i have so much doubt and mistrust and a lot of the time i have no idea where i’m headed.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i don’t think a lot of us do. we just “end up” somewhere and for a moment we might be happy.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#journeyoflife
📸 - @aliciathurstonphotography

node.text:
i think curiosity is normal and tbh questions like these don’t surprise me anymore.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“so you don’t care about health?” of course i do. i care so much. i care so much to the point where i’ve read multiple books on how the body works, taken seminars, actively chat with health experts both personally and professionally. but we’ve narrowed in what health is into such a small box that anything that doesn’t look like that box or fit in that box is deemed unhealthy. health is a journey, not a destination. i have a psycho-social-bio model of health.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“are you promoting obesity?” these one is a weird question because like where does one start lol. i’m assuming when people say this that they don’t mean “you’re promoting a BMI number higher than x” what they mean is “are you promoting the higher health risks associated with higher BMI numbers?” and the answer is of course not. i want everyone to live forever, happy and healthy. but again, i’m not here as a health professional. i’m here to encourage people to love their bodies no matter what their size is regardless of their health. their health is their responsibility and not my business.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“how can you love yourself when you look like that?” easy. i wake up and i choose love instead of hate. for 5 years of baby steps. 1825 years of choosing love over self harm. over a thousand times choosing to appreciate the universe inside me rather than want to diminish it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
“do you think people really need to see this?” this question almost always comes from women. women who are uncomfortable with skin or bodies that are not a size 2. i rarely ever see anyone say this to kylie jenner or kim k but it happens a lot to people with different bodies. the answer is, yes. if i saw my body when i was younger or bodies that are similar, i would have breathed more. my anxiety would have been less. i would have felt more normal.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
have a beautiful day! ☀️💕✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#selflove #selfgrowth #bodyacceptance

node.text:
i must have been about 13 when i went on my first diet.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i had been told that i had this “baby weight” on me and i should be outgrowing it by now. i wasn’t. i was me. i had the body of a kid. soft. breathing. innocent. those were the days when you got excited to watch a movie in class or when summer nights never seemed to end.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my friend and i started to go to the gym. we wouldn’t eat all day and then we’d exercise at night. we had no clue what we were doing. we just knew that eating less meant you weighed less. that skinny people went to the gym. so this must work?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
except things were getting more complicated. high school happened. things got dark. all of a sudden weight was now tied to self worth in explicit ways. people were sexual here. people were angry. weight had to do with all of it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when my weight started fluctuating, no one took me aside to teach me nutrition or the mechanics of joyful movement. people complimented me when i lost weight, people ignored me or condemned me when i put it back on. no one asked why i binged. no one asked “why” in general.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my story isn’t unique.
this happens to millions of people.
and years may go by before they fully start to understand what they are going through.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
may the people in this community who have language and knowledge around these things be the shining light that so many of us didn’t have when we were younger.
may we continue to remind people that their worth is not in the size of their bodies but the size of their morals and values.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
may we continue to be lighthouses for those in the storm 🌦
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#edrecovery #recoveryispossible #selfworth
📸 - @aliciathurstonphotography
